{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require metal detectors and bag and ID checks at all mainline railway stations",
        "additional_details": "The introduction of new security measures at railway stations will allow for greater protections to both passengers and railway staff. This will act as a deterrent for violent crime and also assist railway operators with providing a better experience for passengers. This will also rebuild confidence in rail travel.",
        "background": "The government should ensure all major mainline railway stations, where passengers can board a train that will travel non-stop for more than 15 minutes, are fitted with airport-style security, such as baggage scanners, metal detectors and ID checks.",
